export const WORKSHOP_JDS = {
  "workshop-logistics-supervisor": "Logistics Supervisor job description\nThe Logistics Supervisor is responsible for coordinating the workshop and site end-to-end movement,\nstorage, and setup of materials, equipment, and technology requirements for events. This role ensures\nthat all materials, equipment, and technical resources are sourced, transported, installed, and dismantled\non time and within budget. The supervisor manages a team of logistics personnel and works closely with\nworkshop team, vendors, and site managers to facilitate a seamless activity.\nKey Responsibilities\n• • • • • Workshop & Event Planning:\no\n\nDevelop detailed logistics plans, including timelines, resource allocation, and material\nrequirements for events.\n\no\n\nCreate and manage detailed kit lists for events material and equipment.\n\no\n\nCoordinate with vendors and suppliers to ensure timely delivery of material and\nequipment.\n\nOn-Site Supervision & Execution:\no\n\nSupervise and manage the logistics for events setup, operation, and dismantling.\n\no\n\nEnsure compliance with health and safety standards along all logistics phases.\n\no\n\nAct as the primary point of contact for technical or logistics problems during the event.\n\nInventory & Asset Management:\no\n\nManage the inventory, storage, and maintenance of all event-related materials, ensuring\nequipment is up-and-running at all times.\n\no\n\nConduct inventory audits, cycle counts, and report on stock levels.\n\nTeam & Vendor Management:\no\n\nLead and train logistics staff and assign daily tasks to them according to schedule.\n\no\n\nManage third-party logistics providers (3PL) and vendors to ensure Service Level\nAgreement (SLA) compliance.\n\nBudgeting & Reporting:\no\n\nAssist in developing and adhering to budgets for logistic operations.\n\no\n\nAnalyze logistics data to identify process improvements for better efficiency and costeffectiveness.\n\n\fRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in logistics, warehouse management, or event operations.\n\n• Education: Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain, Logistics, Business Administration, or a related field\npreferred.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in MS Office (especially Excel), ERP systems (e.g., SAP), and logistics\nmanagement software.\n\n• Operational Knowledge: Thorough understanding of transport management, inventory control,\nand warehousing with basic understanding of event construction materials (welding, carpentry,\nprinting, foam, fabric).\n\n• Soft Skills: Strong leadership, communication, problem-solving, and organizational abilities to\nmanage a team under high-pressure, deadline-driven scenarios.\n\n• Personal Skills: Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and\ninterpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Timely delivery: Percentage of compliance to events schedules.\n\n• Budget control: Adherence to event budget and schedules.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\n• Damaged/Shrinkage Rate: Percentage of inventory damaged during storage or transit to/from\nevents.\n\n• Space Utilization Rate: Percentage of storage space used effectively at site.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines\nand to work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.\n\n•",
  "workshop-installation-manager": "Installation Manager Job Description\nThe Installation Manager in the event fabrication workshop is responsible for planning, coordinating, and\noverseeing the onsite setup of custom-built scenic elements, displays, exhibits, and event structures. This\nrole ensures that all projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to the highest quality standards,\nacting as the liaison between the workshop fabrication team and the client on site.\nThe Installation Manager leads the end-to-end execution of onsite installations for events, exhibitions, and\nbrand activations. They are responsible for managing installation crews, coordinating logistics, ensuring\nsafety compliance, and resolving technical challenges during assembly and dismantling.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Project Planning & Onsite Management\n• Site Surveys & Logistics: Conduct site visits to assess venue conditions, plan load-in/load-out\nlogistics, and verify structural requirements.\n\n• Execution Leadership: Plan and direct the installation of projects, ensuring compliance with design\nspecifications and quality standards.\n\n• Timeline Adherence: Manage project schedules to ensure timely completion of setup, rehearsals,\nand dismantling.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Troubleshoot issues in the field, such as unforeseen site obstacles, and\nimplement immediate solutions.\n\n2. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Crew Management: Supervise and lead internal installation teams and external subcontractors,\nfostering a high-performance culture.\n\n• Training & Safety: Enforce safety protocols, conduct toolbox talks, and ensure all staff use proper\nPPE and equipment.\n\n• Performance Evaluation: Monitor team productivity, provide technical guidance, and assess\nperformance.\n\n3. Coordination & Communication\n• Liaison Role: Act as the primary point of contact for clients, project managers, and venue staff\nduring the installation phase.\n\n• Internal Coordination: Work with the workshop team to ensure fabricated items are ready,\npacked, and shipped correctly.\n\n• Reporting: Prepare daily progress reports, snag lists, and post-installation documentation.\n\n4. Quality Control & Resource Management\n\n\f• Quality Inspection: Verify the quality of installation work and ensure it matches approved\ndrawings/samples.\n\n• Asset Management: Maintain inventory of tools, equipment, and consumables used on site.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 10+ years as an installation manager in the event industry, scenery construction, or\nexhibition fabrication industry.\n\n• Technical Skills: Ability to read and interpret technical drawings, blueprints, and CAD files. Strong\nknowledge of carpentry, metal fabrication, branding works and painting.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to manage teams and subcontractors in high-pressure, fast-paced\nenvironments.\n\n• Logistics: Experience with material handling, transport, and site logistics.\n\n• Software: Proficiency in Microsoft Office, with experience in project management tools like MS\nProject or AutoCAD being a plus.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• On-Time Delivery Rate: 100% of projects shipped by the required date.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required on-site.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\n• Budget Adherence: Production costs within ±5% of the initial estimate.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines and\nto work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.",
  "workshop-factory-manager": "Factory manager job description\nThe Factory Manager will ensure that the company policies and procedures are followed and oversees\nall daily operations, ensuring custom event assets are fabricated, finished, and dispatched on time,\nwithin budget, and to the highest quality standards. This role leads the workshop team, coordinates\nmaterials, manages safety compliance, and collaborates with project managers, designers, and onsite\ninstallation crews.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Production Management & Scheduling\n• Plan, organize, and manage day-to-day operations of the workshop, ensuring efficient workflow,\nensuring on-time delivery for event setups, and maintaining production schedules.\n\n• Coordinate with project managers to review shop drawings and technical specs, translating\ndesign concepts into practical production methods.\n\n• Monitor daily production outputs, tracking project milestones, and adjusting schedules to meet\ntight client deadlines.\n\n2. Technical Oversight & Quality Control\n• Insure that the fabrication teams (carpentry, metalwork and welding, printing, foam works,\npainting) are constructing custom, high-end scenic elements.\n\n• Ensure all fabrication works (carpentry, metalwork and welding, printing, foam works, painting)\nmeet company quality standards and client specifications.\n\n• Insure that final inspections and quality checks are conducted before dispatch to the event\nvenue.\n\n3. Team Leadership & Resource Allocation\n• Supervise, mentor, and train workshop staff, fostering a culture of safety, efficiency, and\nteamwork.\n\n• Allocate workforce efficiently to maximize productivity, utilizing overtime only when necessary.\n\n• Conduct performance reviews, provide mentorship, and manage staffing levels based on\nworkload.\n\n4. Safety & Maintenance\n• Enforce strict health and safety (HSE) protocols in the fabrication shop, ensuring compliance with\nOSHA and local regulations.\n\n• Conduct regular safety meetings, tool training, and inspections to maintain a clean, organized,\nand safe working environment.\n\n\f• Maintain workshop machinery, tools, and equipment through scheduled preventative and\ncorrective maintenance.\n\n5. Inventory & Budget Control\n• Establish and monitor inventory levels of raw materials and consumables.\n\n• Coordinate with procurement to order materials, minimizing waste and managing budget\ntargets.\n\n• Document material usage to assist in project costing and job reconciliation.\n\n6. Reporting & Collaboration\n• Prepare and present reports on workshop performance, production metrics, and other key\nperformance indicators to senior management.\n\n• Work closely with other departments (e.g., procurement, sales, engineering) to ensure alignment\non goals and initiatives.\n\nRequirements\n• Experience: 15+ years of experience in an event fabrication, with strong preference for\nexperience in event industry.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in reading engineering drawings, blueprints, and CAD files.\nKnowledge of printing, carpentry, steel fabrication, foam works, and finishing processes.\n\n• Software: Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word) and experience with ERP/MRP systems.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to manage a team, handle high-pressure situations, and meet tight\ndeadlines.\n\n• Education: Bachelor’s degree in Production Management, Industrial Engineering, or related field\npreferred, or equivalent work experience.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• On-Time Delivery Rate: 100% of projects shipped by the required date.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required on-site.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\n• Budget Adherence: Production costs within ±5% of the initial estimate.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n\n\f• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-design-engineer": "Technical Design Engineer Job description\nThe Technical Design Engineer role for the production workshop in event industry will be responsible\nfor translating creative concepts into detailed, build-ready technical drawings (CAD) for events,\nexhibitions, and activations. You will act as the bridge between the design team and the workshop\nproduction team, ensuring that all custom fabrication is safe, compliant with health & safety\nregulations, and executed efficiently.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Technical Design & Drafting: Produce detailed production drawings, 3D concepts, and\nconstruction plans using AutoCAD/SolidWorks for workshop fabrication and on-site use .\nPerform / review structural analysis and load calculations to ensure structural integrity of\ncustom event structures, rigging points, and suspended elements.\n\n• Prototyping & Testing: Design and develop prototypes for custom scenic elements, jigs, and\nfixtures to facilitate efficient assembly.\n\n• Feasibility & Compliance: Ensure all designs are structurally sound, compliant with event\nregulations, and adhere to Health & Safety standards.\n\n• Production Liaison: Collaborate closely with the project manager and workshop technicians\nto optimize workflows, solve construction challenges, and ensure quality control and manage\ncosts.\n\n• Material Management: Research, select, and manage materials for construction. Create Bills\nof Materials (BOM).\n\n• Documentation: Maintain accurate, up-to-date engineering records, technical files, and \"asbuilt\" drawings.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in custom fabrication, scenic construction, exhibition\ndesign, or event production.\n\n• Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Industrial Design, or a related field\nor equivalent.\n\n• Software Proficiency: Advanced proficiency in 3D CAD software (SolidWorks or Inventor) and\n2D AutoCAD and Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator/Photoshop) for conceptualizing.\n\n• Technical Knowledge: Strong understanding of manufacturing processes (sheet metal, CNC\nmachining, carpentry) and material properties.\n\n\f• Problem-Solving: Ability to solve complex technical problems in a fast-paced, deadline-driven\nenvironment.\n\n• Hands-on Attitude: A willingness to be on the shop floor, supporting the production team\nand testing prototypes.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• On-Time Delivery Rate: On-time delivery (OTD) of projects designs and reduction in redesign\niterations and time.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required due to design issues.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents due to design issues.\n\n• Budget Adherence: Production cost within ±5% of the initial estimate.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud\nnoise, dust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight\ndeadlines.",
  "workshop-production-manager": "Production Manager job description\nThe Production Manager for the event fabrication workshop is responsible for overseeing the entire\nproduction cycle of event structures, exhibition stands, sets, and custom props, from initial design\ninterpretation to final installation. This role bridges the gap between design, client servicing, and onground fabrication, ensuring projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to high quality\nstandards.\nThe ideal candidate is an experienced leader with a strong background in workshop operations\n(carpentry, metalwork, printing, foam work, and painting) who can manage daily production workflows,\nlead a team of multidiscipline works, and ensure safety compliance.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Production Planning & Workflow: Develop and manage production schedules based on factory\ncapacity, ensuring on-time delivery of projects.\n\n• Design Interpretation: Review technical drawings and liaise with the design team to ensure\nproduction feasibility.\n\n• Team Leadership: Supervise, train, and mentor workshop staff, including carpenters, , metal\nfabricators, printers, painters.\n\n• Resource & Inventory Management: Determine necessary material resources, manage inventory\nlevels, and optimize usage to reduce wastage.\n\n• Budgeting & Cost Control: Monitor project budgets, prepare cost estimates, and implement\nstrategies to save money on materials and labor.\n\n• Quality Control: Establish and enforce quality standards, inspecting final outputs before dispatch\nor installation.\n\n• Health, Safety & Compliance (HSE): Enforce strict safety protocols, maintain a clean, organized\nwork environment, and ensure compliance with health and safety legislation.\n\n• Logistics & Site Coordination: Preplan and oversee the installation and dismantlement of\nprojects on-site.\n\n• Reporting: Submit weekly reports to management regarding project status, milestones, and\nachievements.\n\nKey Requirements & Skills\n• 10+ years as a production manager in event industry, with carpentry, metalwork, printing, foam\nwork, and painting shops.\n\n• Deep understanding of fabrication techniques (wood, metal, printing, foam, and painting) and\nmaterial sourcing.\n\n\f• Experience with MS Office and, ideally, CAD software or ERP systems.\n\n• Strong team management abilities to foster a productive and safe work culture.\n\n• Ability to resolve production bottlenecks and adapt to changing timelines.\n\n• Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Production Management, or related field is often preferred,\nbut extensive practical experience is highly valued.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• On-Time Delivery Rate: 100% of projects shipped by the required date.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required on-site.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\n• Budget Adherence: Production costs within ±5% of the initial estimate.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-quality-manager": "Quality Manager Job Description\nThe Quality Manager in the event fabrication workshop will ensure that custom-built, event structures\nmeet client specifications, safety standards, and structural integrity requirements before leaving the\nworkshop and thereafter at the site. This role bridges the gap between creative design, project\nmanagement, and structural safety.\nThe Quality Manager will establish, implement, and maintain rigorous quality assurance control\nprocedures for all fabrication, from raw materials to final, installed products. The role involves inspecting\nbespoke designs, ensuring structural safety, and fostering a \"correct at source\" culture to reduce rework,\nmeet tight installation deadlines, and maximize client satisfaction.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Quality System Management: Develop, document, and enforce a quality management system\nwith standard operating procedures (SOPs) for carpentry, metal fabrication, printing, foam, and\npainting, and assembly at workshop and site.\n\n• Pre-Production/Design Review: Participate in design reviews to ensure feasibility, identify\npotential structural issues, and ensure compliance with safety, legal, and environmental\nstandards.\n\n• In-Process Inspections: Conduct routine, in-process audits of fabrication work to identify\ndeviations early.\n\n• Final Inspection & Release: Inspect completed, bespoke event structures for cosmetic, structural,\nand functional compliance before shipping.\n\n• Supplier & Material Quality: Inspect incoming raw materials to ensure they meet specifications.\n\n• Corrective Action & Rework: Lead investigations into non-conforming items, identify root causes,\nand implement corrective actions to prevent recurrence.\n\n• Health & Safety Compliance: Work with the production team to ensure all fabrications adhere to\nhealth and safety regulations, including electrical safety for scenic elements.\n\n• Documentation: Maintain accurate records for client certifications, material traceability, and\nsafety audits.\n\n• Project Liaison: Coordinate with project managers and clients to resolve quality issues and\nmanage expectations.\n\nRequired Skills & Experience\n• Experience: 10+ years as a Quality Assurance / Quality manager, preferably in event fabrication\nand construction environments.\n\n• Technical Knowledge: Strong understanding of metal fabrication (welding) and/or carpentry,\nfinishing techniques, and technical drawing/blueprint interpretation.\n\n\f• Certifications: ISO 9001 lead auditor training is highly desirable.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Ability to resolve complex technical issues under tight deadlines.\n\n• Leadership: Experience leading a small team of technicians, inspectors, or assemblers.\n\n• Computer Skills: Proficiency in MS Office (Excel) for reporting, interpretation of engineering\ndrawings, and experience with CAD/CAM software is a plus.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Rework & scrap: Minimal rework hours and material scrap.\n\n• Inspection: Timely completion of inspection reports and in-process audits.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required on-site.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines\nand to work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.",
  "workshop-printing-team-leader": "Printing Team Leader Job description\nThe Printing Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the printing section in\nthe event production workshop for producing high-quality, large-format graphics, signage, and\nbranding materials for events, exhibitions, and activations, in an efficiently, safely, and to high-quality\nstandards. This hands-on role involves leading a team of printers, , acting as the primary link between\nthe production Manager / Designers and the workshop floor. This role requires setting up, operating,\nand maintaining digital printers, vinyl cutters, and finishing equipment, often under tight deadlines to\nmeet client specifications.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and\ngoals.\n\n2. Production & Operational efficiency\n• Interpret technical drawings, CAD drawings, and design briefs to guide fabrication.\n\n• Coordinate workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and downtime.\n\n• Operate large format inkjet printers, UV flatbed printers, and vinyl plotters (e.g., Durst, HP\nLatex, …).\n\n• Prepare machines for daily operations: loading substrate rolls (vinyl, banner, fabric), preparing\nink supplies, and verifying job specifications.\n\n• Monitor printing processes to ensure accuracy, color consistency, and registration throughout\nthe run.\n\n• Maintain high-speed production of materials, including banners, vinyl wraps, posters, and\ndisplay graphics.\n\n• Collaborate with project managers to update them on progress, potential delays, or material\nissues.\n\n• Perform, or assist in, post-print finishing tasks: trimming, laminating, mounting to rigid\nsubstrates (foam core, PVC, Dibond), and weeding vinyl.\n\n\f3.Quality Control & Safety\n• Enforce strict health and safety rules, including wearing PPE and maintaining a 5S compliant,\norderly workspace.\n\n• Perform quality checks on finished prints to identify and correct imperfections, such as ink\nstarvation, banding, or color misalignment, ensuring they meet client specifications before\nleaving the workshop.\n\n4. Maintenance & Safety\n• Perform daily, weekly, and monthly maintenance on equipment (cleaning printheads,\nlubricating gears) to minimize downtime.\n\n• Troubleshoot mechanical issues and, if necessary, coordinate with service technicians for\nrepairs.\n\n• Maintain a clean and safe, organized work environment, including proper handling and\ndisposal of inks, solvents, and chemicals.\n\n5.Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Ensure all equipment (saws, welders, routers, …) are maintained and in good working order.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience as a printing team leader for a high-quality, large-format\ngraphics, signage, and branding materials for events, exhibitions, and activations.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n\f• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-steel-fabricator": "Steel Fabricator Job description\nThe Steel Fabricator in the event industry (stages, set design, exhibition stands) is responsible for\ninterpreting technical drawings to cut, weld, and assemble custom metal structures for stages, set\ndesign, exhibition stands and the like. Unlike general construction, this role requires working closely\nwith production leaders and designers to bring custom and creative designs to life, ensuring\neverything is safe, precise, and delivered on time. This roll requires high flexibility, rapid turnaround\ntimes, and attention to finish quality for structures that will be highly visible to the public.\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Fabrication & Assembly: Cut, shape, weld, and assemble steel components (e.g., custom\nstructures, rigging frames, scenic elements, support structures) using MIG/TIG welding,\ngrinders, and plasma cutters.\n\n• Technical Interpretation: Read and interpret CAD drawings, blueprints, and engineering\nspecifications to ensure accurate fabrication.\n\n• Quality Control: Inspect and measure finished components to ensure structural integrity and\ncompliance with safety standards before they leave the workshop.\n\n• Material Handling: Safely operate workshop machinery (brake presses, shears, drills) and\nmaterial handling equipment (forklifts, overhead cranes).\n\n• Customization & Finishing: Perform grinding and finishing to ensure smooth, aesthetically\npleasing, or paint-ready finishes for public-facing structures.\n\n• Collaboration: Coordinate with on-site installation teams to ensure components fit together\nseamlessly.\n\n• Maintenance: Maintain a clean, organized work area and perform routine maintenance on\ntools and machinery.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in metal fabrication, preferably with custom or lightstructural steel projects.\n\n• Education: High school diploma; technical school or welding certification preferred.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in MIG/TIG/stick welding.\n\n• Blueprint Reading: Strong ability to read technical drawings and shop layouts.\n\n• Precision: Excellent attention to detail for precise, custom work.\n\n• Physical Stamina: Ability to stand for long periods, lift heavy objects, and work in varied\nphysical positions.\n\n\fIdeal Candidate Profile:\n• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight\ndeadlines.",
  "workshop-store-keeper": "Store keeper job description\nThe Store Keeper in an event industry workshop is responsible for managing the receipt, storage,\nmaintenance, and issuance of materials, tools, and equipment used for events, exhibitions, and fit-out\nprojects. This role ensures that all necessary items are available on time, properly organized, and wellmaintained to ensure smooth event production.\nKey Responsibilities\nReceiving, Issuing & Dispatch\n• Receive Goods: Verify incoming materials against purchase orders and delivery notes, inspecting\nfor damage or discrepancies.\n\n• Issue Materials: Release materials and tools to production, installation, and site teams based on\napproved requests.\n\n• Logistics Support: Coordinate the packing and loading of equipment for transport to event\nvenues.\n\n• Returns Management: Process returned items from event sites, inspecting them and returning\nthem to proper storage.\n\nInventory Control & Management\n• Track Stock Levels: Maintain accurate, up-to-date records of all materials, tools, equipment, and\nconsumables.\n\n• Inventory Audits: Conduct regular, daily, and monthly physical stock counts and reconcile them\nwith system records.\n\n• Stock Organization: Arrange, label, and identify stock items for quick retrieval.\n\n• Monitor Stock Levels: Prevent shortages or overstocking of critical materials and manage stock\naging to avoid waste.\n\nWorkshop & Safety Maintenance\n• Housekeeping: Maintain a clean, organized, and safe warehouse/workshop area.\n\n• Asset Care: Inspect equipment for damage, ensuring tools are safe for use.\n\n• Safety Compliance: Adhere to fire safety regulations and handle hazardous or heavy materials\nproperly.\n\nDocumentation & Reporting\n• Record Keeping: Maintain stock registers, bin cards, and computerized records of all\ntransactions.\n\n\f• Reporting: Prepare daily, weekly, and monthly stock reports for management.\n\n• Documentation: Process Material Received Reports (MRR) and Stock Issue Vouchers (SIV).\n\nRequired Qualification & Skills\n• Minimum 5+ years of experience as a store keeper, preferably in an event fabrication\nenvironment.\n\n• Bachelor degree/diploma or equivalent is required in warehouse / logistics management,\nbusiness administration, or any related field.\n\n• Proficiency in Warehouse Management Systems (WMS) and Microsoft office.\n\n• Excellent leadership skills with the ability to manage a team under high-pressure, deadlinedriven scenarios.\n\n• Exceptional problem-solving abilities to handle tight deadlines and unexpected, last-minute\nproject changes.\n\n• Basic understanding of event construction materials (welding, carpentry, printing, foam, fabric).\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Stock Availability: Ensuring materials are always available according to stock levels.\n\n• Inventory Accuracy Rate: Variance between physical stock and system records (critical for highvalue props/materials).\n\n• Timely delivery: Percentage of items delivered/loaded on time for a specific event with no delay.\n\n• Damaged/Shrinkage Rate: Percentage of inventory damaged during storage or transit to/from\nevents.\n\n• Space Utilization Rate: Percentage of storage space used effectively, especially during peak\nfabrication cycles.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines\nand to work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.",
  "workshop-installation-team-leader": "Installation Team Leader Job description\nThe Installation Team Leader for the fabrication workshop in event industry is responsible for the onsite execution of the project. He will coordinate with other departments to insure that fabricated\nassemblies, events sets, equipment, and scenic elements are shipped and installed safely, to high\nquality, on time, and within budget. This is a hands-on leadership role requiring technical proficiency\nin site construction combined with the ability to motivate the site team.\nKey Responsibilities\nProduction & Supervision\n• Workflow Management: Prepare the plan and schedule for the project in hand.\n\n• Pre-fabrication & Assembly: Ensure all components are built /pre-assembled /and tested, as\nrequired, in the workshop before being dispatched to the venue.\n\n• Packing & Loading: Supervise the packing, loading, and securement of event assets onto\ntransport to prevent damage during transit.\n\n• Resource Management: Monitor manpower, materials, and tools and secure them as\nrequired.\n\n• Quality Control: Inspect fabricated and assembled items and equipment to ensure they meet\ndesign specifications, safety regulations, and client quality standards.\n\nHealth, Safety & Compliance\n• Risk Management: Develop or enforce Risk Assessments and Method Statements (RAMS) for\non-site installations.\n\n• Safety Enforcement: Ensure all team members comply with Health and Safety policies,\nincluding the use of PPE and safe handling of machinery (e.g., CNC, saws, welding gear).\n\n• Housekeeping: Maintain a clean, organized, and safe site environment (5S standards).\n\nTeam Leadership & Communication\n• On-site Leadership: Lead daily site operations and allocate daily tasks to fabricators,\ncarpenters, and technicians, ensuring efficient use of manpower to meet project deadlines.\n\n• Coaching & Mentoring: Train and mentor junior staff on fabrication techniques, tool safety,\nand company procedures.\n\n• Performance Monitoring: Conduct team briefings, monitor performance, and provide\nfeedback to improve efficiency and reduce rework.\n\n• Project Liaison: Liaise with project managers, designers, and site management to provide\nupdates, resolve bottlenecks, and ensure project success.\n\n\fQualifications & Skills\n• Experience: 5+ years of proven experience in event production, theatrical scenic construction,\nexhibition fabrication, or a similar workshop environment.\n\n• Technical Skills: Deep knowledge of carpentry, metalwork, rigging, AV, lighting, or scenic paint\ntechniques.\n\n• Blueprint Interpretation: Ability to read and interpret technical drawings, CAD files, and\ndesign specifications.\n\n• Safety Certifications: Relevant H&S qualifications (e.g., IOSH, OSHA, IPAF, or PASMA).\n\n• Soft Skills: Strong leadership, ability to work under pressure, proactive problem-solving, and\nexcellent communication.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight\ndeadlines.",
  "workshop-painter": "Painter Job description\nThe painter in an event industry fabrication workshop is responsible for prepping, painting, and\nfinishing custom-built scenic elements, props, displays, and structures. They operate in a fast-paced\nenvironment to meet strict production deadlines, often applying specialized coatings to wood, metal,\nand plastics. The role involves high-quality spray painting, color matching, and maintaining a clean, safe\nworkshop environment.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Surface Preparation: Clean, sand, scrape, fill holes/cracks with putty, and prime various\nmaterials (wood, metal, foam, plastics) to ensure a smooth finish.\n\n• Application Techniques: Apply paint, enamel, varnish, and lacquers using spray guns, rollers,\nand brushes.\n\n• Specialized Finishes: Create custom scenic finishes, faux textures, and effects as required by\nscenic designers.\n\n• Color Matching: Mix and match colors to meet specific, often custom, design requirements.\n\n• Quality Control: Inspect finished surfaces for imperfections, ensuring high-quality, durable, and\naesthetically pleasing results.\n\n• Equipment Maintenance: Clean, maintain, and troubleshoot painting equipment, including\nspray booths, airbrushes, and air-assisted airless sprayers.\n\n• Workshop Safety: Comply with HSE standards at the work space, including proper\nstorage/disposal of chemicals and use of PPE (respirators, goggles).\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of professional painting experience, preferably in an industrial, fabrication,\nor scenic shop.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency with various spray equipment, power tools, and sanders.\n\n• Attention to Detail: Exceptional focus on achieving high-quality, detailed finishes.\n\n• Versatility: Ability to switch between tasks and work on multiple projects simultaneously.\n\n• Physical Stamina: Ability to lift heavy objects, stand for long periods, and work in varied\ntemperatures.\n\nIdeal Candidate Profile:\n• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n\f• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-foam-team-leader": "Foam Fabrication Team Leader Job description\nThe Foam Sculpturing / Fabrication Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of\nthe Foam Fabrication section in the event fabrication workshop, aiming at transforming raw EPS\n(Expanded Polystyrene) or polyurethane foam into detailed 3D props, scenic elements, and large-scale\nstructures for corporate events, trade shows, theatrical sets, and themed attractions. The role involves\ninterpreting design sketches or blueprints and using a combination of CNC-cut components and skilled\nmanual hand-carving to produce visually stunning, durable, and lightweight props, ensuring that\nelements are fabricated efficiently, safely, and to high-quality standards. This hands-on role involves\nleading a team of foam fabricators, acting as the primary link between the production Managers /\nDesigners and the workshop floor.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and\ngoals.\n\n2. Production & Operational Efficiency\n• Blueprint Interpretation: Interpret technical drawings, 3D models, or artistic sketches and\ndesign to translate concepts into accurately scaled, physical props to guide fabrication.\n\n• Coordination: Coordinate workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and\ndowntime.\n\n• Foam Carving & Shaping: Carve, shape, and sculpt foam (EPS, PU) into 3D models using 3D\nrobots, hot wire cutters, rasps, rotary tools, and hand saws.\n\n• Structural Assembly: Assemble multiple foam blocks, gluing, fitting, and clamping parts to\ncreate large-scale structures, ensuring structural integrity for transport and installation.\n\n• Detailing & Finishing: Apply fine details to foam surfaces using hand tools (e.g., Dremel tools)\nto create textures like wood grain, stone, or character features.\n\n• Surface Coating: Apply hard-coating materials (such as polyurea, epoxy resins, or sand-coat) to\nensure durability for indoor/outdoor display.\n\n• Collaboration: Work closely with designers, painters, and welders to integrate steel armatures\nor electrical components into foam sculptures. Collaborate with project managers to update\nthem on progress, potential delays, or material issues.\n\n\f• Support, and sometimes lead, on-site installation or load-in/out during high-pressure times.\n\n• Tool Maintenance & Safety: Clean and maintain specialized workshop machinery (3d robots\nand hot wires) and adhering to strict safety protocols and PPE requirements.\n\n3. Quality Control & Safety\n• Enforce strict health and safety rules, including wearing PPE and maintaining a 5S compliant,\norderly workspace.\n\n• Inspect finished products and assemblies for defects, ensuring they meet client specifications\nbefore leaving the workshop.\n\n• Identify and resolve technical fabrication issues early to prevent delays.\n\n4. Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Ensure all equipment (saws, welders, routers, …) are maintained and in good working order.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of professional experience in foam sculpting, prop-making, or scenic art,\npreferably in the event or film industry.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Technical Proficiency: Expert skill with hand-carving tools, operating 3D robots, hot wires,\nsanders, and adhesive applications.\n\n• Spatial Awareness: Exceptional ability to visualize 3D forms from 2D drawings or CAD data.\n\n• Artistic Talent: Strong understanding of form, texture, and proportion, proficiency in scenic\npainting and texturing techniques.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\n• Efficiency: Ability to work quickly to meet strict event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Stamina: Ability to stand for long periods and handle large materials.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\n\fKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-warehouse-manager": "Warehouse Manager job description\nThe Warehouse Manager will work in a fast-paced, bespoke environment that involves building custom\nevent sets, props, furniture, and structures. Unlike standard distribution, this role requires managing\nraw materials (wood, metal, foam, textiles) alongside high-value finished, fragile event assets, and\nmanaging tight, project-based deadlines.\nWarehouse Manager will be a highly organized with hands-on experience to oversee the daily\noperations of our event fabrication workshop. The ideal candidate will manage the receiving, storage,\nand dispatch of raw materials and finished custom builds, ensuring that props, furniture, and event\nstructures are securely stored and delivered on time to job sites. He will maintain inventory accuracy,\nlead the warehouse team, and ensure a safe, efficient working environment, collaborating closely with\ninstallation and project managers to meet tight project deadlines.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Logistics & Project Coordination: Coordinate with workshop managers to plan for inbound and\noutbound materials.\n\n• Logistics & Project Coordination: Coordinate with installation and project managers to plan for\ninbound materials and outbound, high-priority delivery of finished fabrication projects to event\nsites.\n\n• Inventory & Stock Control: Manage, track, and conduct regular audits of stock levels for raw\nmaterials (lumber, metal, foam, fabric), consumables, inventory of custom-built, rental, or\nreusable event assets, and spare parts.\n\n• Storage & Facility Management: Implement and optimize storage layouts for large-scale,\nunique, or fragile event pieces to maximize space and ensure easy access.\n\n• Shipping & Receiving: Inspect incoming raw materials for quality and quantity, and oversee the\npacking, loading, and secure transport of finished goods to project locations.\n\n• Team Leadership & Safety: Lead, train, and supervise warehouse staff. Ensure compliance with\nOSHA standards, and maintain a safe, clean, and orderly work environment (including tool\nmaintenance).\n\n• Equipment Operation: Oversee the operation of machinery, including forklifts, high-reach\nvehicles, and pallet jacks to load/unload trucks.\n\n• Record Keeping: Maintain digital inventory records, delivery documentation, and project\ntracking reports.\n\nRequired Qualification & Skills\n• Minimum 10+ years of warehouse management experience, preferably in an event fabrication\nenvironment.\n\n\f• Bachelor’s degree in warehouse / logistics management, business administration, or any related\nfield.\n\n• Strong proficiency in Warehouse Management Systems (WMS) and Microsoft office.\n\n• Excellent leadership skills with the ability to manage a team under high-pressure, deadlinedriven scenarios.\n\n• Exceptional problem-solving abilities to handle tight deadlines and unexpected, last-minute\nproject changes.\n\n• Basic understanding of event construction materials (welding, carpentry, printing, foam, fabric).\n\n• Ability to resolve complex technical issues under tight deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Inventory Accuracy Rate: Variance between physical stock and system records (critical for highvalue props/materials).\n\n• Timely delivery: Percentage of items loaded on time for a specific event with no delay.\n\n• Pick Accuracy (Load Accuracy): Percentage of items loaded correctly for a specific event.\n\n• Damaged/Shrinkage Rate: Percentage of inventory damaged during storage or transit to/from\nevents.\n\n• Space Utilization Rate: Percentage of storage space used effectively, especially during peak\nfabrication cycles.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines\nand to work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.",
  "workshop-carpentry-team-leader": "Carpentry Team Leader Job description\nThe Carpentry Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of Carpentry section in\nthe event fabrication workshop and ensuring that scenic elements, structures, custom displays, and\nrelated furniture are fabricated efficiently, safely, and to high-quality standards. This hands-on role\ninvolves leading a team of Carpenters as the primary link between the Production Manager /\nDesigners and the workshop floor.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and\ngoals.\n\n2. Production & Operational Efficiency\n• Fabrication & Assembly: Build, repair, and modify scenery, exhibit stands, and props using\nwood, laminates, plastics, and sometimes metal.\n\n• Blueprint Interpretation: Read, interpret, and work from technical drawings, CAD drawings, or\nsketches provided by designers.\n\n• Finishing Work: Apply high-quality finishes, including painting, laminating, and trimming,\nensuring items are \"show-ready\".\n\n• Tool Maintenance: Safely operate and maintain all shop equipment (table saws, routers, CNC\nmachines, pneumatic tools).\n\n• Logistics Support: Load/unload trucks, pack items securely for transport, and assist with onsite installation and strikes.\n\n• Collaboration: Work with project managers and other technicians to meet tight deadlines.\n\n• Coordinate workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and downtime.\n\n• Support, and sometimes lead, on-site installation or load-in/out during high-pressure times.\n\n3. Quality Control & Safety\n• Enforce strict health and safety rules, including wearing PPE and maintaining a 5S compliant,\norderly workspace.\n\n\f• Inspect finished products and assemblies for defects, ensuring they meet client specifications\nbefore leaving the workshop.\n\n• Identify and resolve technical fabrication issues early to prevent delays.\n\n4. Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Ensure all equipment are maintained and in good working order.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in carpentry scenic construction, exhibit fabrication, or a\nsimilar high-paced workshop environment.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in reading technical drawings and experience with woodworking or\nscenic painting.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-printing-operator": "Printing Operator Job Description\nA Printing Operator in an event industry fabrication workshop is responsible for producing highquality, large-format graphics, signage, and branding materials for events, exhibitions, and activations.\nThis role requires setting up, operating, and maintaining digital printers, vinyl cutters, and finishing\nequipment, often under tight deadlines to meet client specifications.\nKey Responsibilities\nMachine Operation & Setup\n• Operate large format inkjet printers, UV flatbed printers, and vinyl plotters (e.g., Durst, HP\nLatex, …).\n\n• Prepare machines for daily operations: loading substrate rolls (vinyl, banner, fabric), preparing\nink supplies, and verifying job specifications.\n\n• Configure printer settings via software (e.g., ONYX, Caldera) to ensure correct color,\nresolution, and print quality.\n\nProduction & Quality Control\n• Monitor printing processes to ensure accuracy, color consistency, and registration throughout\nthe run.\n\n• Perform quality checks on finished prints to identify and correct imperfections, such as ink\nstarvation, banding, or color misalignment.\n\n• Maintain high-speed production of materials, including banners, vinyl wraps, posters, and\ndisplay graphics.\n\nFinishing & Post-Processing\n• Perform, or assist in, post-print finishing tasks: trimming, laminating, mounting to rigid\nsubstrates (foam core, PVC, Dibond), and weeding vinyl.\n\n• Prepare graphics for, or assist with, application/installation at event venues.\n\nMaintenance & Safety\n• Perform daily, weekly, and monthly maintenance on equipment (cleaning printheads,\nlubricating gears) to minimize downtime.\n\n• Troubleshoot mechanical issues and, if necessary, coordinate with service technicians for\nrepairs.\n\n• Maintain a clean and safe, organized work environment, including proper handling and\ndisposal of inks, solvents, and chemicals.\n\n\fRequirements & Skills\n• Experience: Proven 5+ years of experience as a large format printer operator, ideally within a\nprint shop or fabrication environment.\n\n• Education: High school diploma; technical school or welding certification preferred.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency with RIP software (ONYX, Caldera) and Adobe Creative Suite\n(Illustrator, Photoshop).\n\n• Knowledge: Strong understanding of print media, substrates, and ink types.\n\n• Mechanical Aptitude: Ability to perform basic equipment maintenance and troubleshooting.\n\n• Precision: Exceptional attention to detail, specifically regarding color accuracy and cutting\nprecision.\n\n• Physical Strength: Ability to lift heavy materials and stand for extended periods.\n\n• Flexibility: Capacity to work under high pressure, meet tight, fast-paced, and changing\ndeadlines.\n\n• Communication: Effective communication skills to collaborate with designers and project\nmanagers.\n\nIdeal Candidate Profile:\n• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight\ndeadlines.",
  "workshop-carpenter": "Carpenter Job Description\nThe Carpenter in the event industry fabrication workshop is responsible for interpreting designs,\nconstructing, and finishing custom scenic elements, exhibitions, props, and furniture. Unlike traditional\nconstruction, this role requires working closely with production leaders and designers to bring custom\nand creative designs to life, ensuring everything is safe, precise, and delivered on time. This roll\nrequires high flexibility, rapid turnaround times, and attention to finish quality for structures that will\nbe highly visible to the public. .\nKey Responsibilities\n• Fabrication & Assembly: Build, repair, and modify scenery, exhibit stands, and props using\nwood, laminates, plastics, and sometimes metal.\n\n• Blueprint Interpretation: Read, interpret, and work from technical drawings, CAD drawings, or\nsketches provided by designers.\n\n• Finishing Work: Apply high-quality finishes, including painting, laminating, and trimming,\nensuring items are \"show-ready\".\n\n• Tool Maintenance: Safely operate and maintain all shop equipment (table saws, routers, CNC\nmachines, pneumatic tools).\n\n• Logistics Support: Load/unload trucks, pack items securely for transport, and assist with onsite installation and strikes.\n\n• Collaboration: Work with project managers and other technicians to meet tight deadlines.\n\nRequired Qualifications & Skills\n• Experience: 3+ years of experience in scenic carpentry, and custom exhibit fabrication.\n\n• Education: High school diploma; technical school.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in woodworking, reading technical blueprints, and operating a\nwide range of shop tools.\n\n• Material Knowledge: Familiarity with various materials, including timber, MDF, plywood,\nplastics, steel, and aluminum.\n\n• Physical Stamina: Ability to lift loads, work at heights, and stand for long periods.\n\n• Certifications: Valid driver’s license; forklift or rigging experience is a plus.\n\n• Safety: Requires a high level of safety awareness to prevent accidents in a busy shop\nenvironment.\n\nIdeal Candidate Profile:\n\n\f• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-engineering-manager": "Engineering Manager Job description\nThe Engineering Manager for the Event Fabrication Workshop creates custom design and structure\ndisplays, trade show booths, set pieces, and scenic elements. This role merges creative fabrication,\nstructural engineering, and fast-paced project management. In doing this, he will act as the crucial link\nbetween conceptual designers, project management, and the fabrication workshop floor\nThe Engineering Manager leads the technical team of designers and engineers to translate artistic\nconcepts into safe, structural, and buildable events, exhibitions, and scenic structures. This role oversees\nthe entire technical lifecycle for the product covering conceptual design, CAD design, shop drawings,\nmaterial selection, and structural analysis. This while meeting the standard safety requirements,\nproducing most economic and practical designs, and meeting the required quality standard. He will\nensure projects are designed to be delivered on time, within budget, and to the highest safety and\nquality standards.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Design & Technical Leadership:\n\n• Lead a team of engineers to generate briefs and design renderings.\n\n• Oversee the translation of client / in-house generated briefs and designer renderings into\naccurate 2D/3D shop drawings (AutoCAD, Inventor, SolidWorks).\n\n• Perform / review structural analysis and load calculations to ensure structural integrity of custom\nevent structures and the structural calculations for custom structures, rigging points, and\nsuspended elements.\n\n• Implement \"Design for fabrication\" (DFM) principles to optimize efficiency, material usage, and\ncost to meet project budget.\n\n• Review all fabrication drawings and technical documents before releasing them to production.\n\n• Insure that workshop production people fully understand the produced designs and that the\nexecution is going smoothly.\n\n2. Production & Workshop Coordination\n• Collaborate with the Workshop Fabrication Manager to ensure designs are optimized for\nproduction, efficiency, and cost-effectiveness (Design for Manufacturability - DFM).\n\n• Generate Bills of Materials (BOMs) and CNC machine programs (e.g., nesting, router paths) via\nCAM software.\n\n4. Project Management & Client Interaction\n• Liaise with project managers and clients to identify design requirements, technical specs, and\npotential risks.\n\n\f• Manage the Engineering Change Notices (ECN) process, ensuring revisions are properly\ndocumented and communicated.\n\n• Conduct site inspections, when required, to ensure installation matches design intent.\n\n5. Team Leadership & Safety:\n• Ensure all products meet safety codes (e.g., fire safety, structural safety for public venues).\n\n• Check in-process and final quality to ensure adherence to client specifications.\n\n• Lead, mentor, and supervise a team of designers and engineers.\n\n• Develop training programs, monitor team performance, and foster a culture of optimized cost,\nefficient productivity, quality and safety in designing the product.\n\n6. Budget & Procurement:\n• Assist project managers with technical cost estimations and materials budgeting.\n\n• Coordinate with procurement for raw materials, hardware, and specialized items.\n\nRequired Qualifications & Skills\n• Experience: 10+ years of experience as an engineering manager at a custom event fabrication and\nscenic workshop environment.\n\n• Technical Knowledge: Strong understanding of materials engineering (metals, plastics, wood) and\nfabrication processes of metal (MIG/TIG welding), carpentry, foam, printing, painting, and\nstructural requirements.\n\n• Software Proficiency: Advanced skills in AutoCAD, SolidWorks, Inventor, SAP.\n\n• Education: Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical or structural Engineering, or related field.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Ability to resolve complex technical challenges under tight deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• On-Time Delivery Rate: On-time delivery (OTD) of projects designs.\n\n• Reduction in redesign iterations and time.\n\n• Quality Rejection Rate: Minimal to no rework required due to design issues.\n\n• Safety Record: Zero lost-time incidents due to design issues.\n\n• Budget Adherence: Production cost within ±5% of the initial estimate.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n\n\f• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-tailor": "Tailor/Seamstress Job Description\nThe Tailor/Seamstress, unlike traditional fashion tailoring, is responsible to produce large-scale\nproduction, scenic elements, drapery, event decor, and quick, durable, and creative repairs, often\noperating under strict, fast-paced deadlines. He will not be creating apparel but rather producing\nhigh-quality and custom fabric installations for event production, scenic design, and trade shows. He\nwill interpret design sketches, work with a variety of materials, and ensure all items are productionready, durable, and aesthetically impeccable.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Fabrication & Production: Measure, cut, and sew large-scale fabric elements including, but\nnot limited to event drapery, stage curtains, custom tablecloths, cushions, and bespoke scenic\nprops.\n\n• Fabric Manipulation: Experience working with a wide range of materials, including heavy-duty\nfabrics (velour, canvas), sheer fabrics (voile, organza), vinyl, and specialized decor fabrics.\n\n• Pattern Making & Cutting: Create custom patterns from designer sketches or blueprints and\nlay out/cut fabric with precision to meet exact dimensions.\n\n• Upholstery & Repairs: Perform on-site or in-shop repairs on furniture, pipe-and-drape\nsystems, and props, including replacing zippers, fasteners, and repairing tears.\n\n• Quality Control: Inspect finished items to ensure they meet high-quality standards and are\ndurable enough for transportation and event installation.\n\n• Collaborative Work: Work closely with the carpentry, scenic, and decorating teams to\nintegrate fabric elements with metal or wood structures.\n\n• Time Management: Deliver high-quality work within tight, often last-minute event deadlines.\n\n• Equipment Maintenance: Operate and maintain industrial sewing machines, sergers, and\nsteamers.\n\n• Safety: Maintain a clean, safe, and organized workspace, adhering to all safety protocols.\n\nRequired Qualifications & Skills\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience as a tailor, seamstress, or scenic stitcher, ideally in in event\ntheatrical drapery or event upholstery, manufacturing, or production environment.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in operating industrial sewing machines, including straight stitch,\noverlock, and blind hem machines.\n\n• Attention to Detail: Exceptional precision in measuring and cutting to ensure a perfect fit for\nevent installations.\n\n• Adaptability: Ability to handle, work with, and troubleshoot unfamiliar or specialty materials.\n\n\f• Physical Stamina: Ability to stand for long periods, lift heavy rolls of fabric, and work in a fastpaced environment.\n\n• Communication: Strong verbal communication skills to work effectively within a team.\n\nIdeal Candidate Profile:\n• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include\nloud noise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight\ndeadlines.",
  "workshop-foam-fabricator": "Foam Sculptor/Fabricator Job Description\nThe Foam Sculptor/ Fabricator is responsible for transforming raw EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) or\npolyurethane foam into detailed 3D props, scenic elements, and large-scale structures for corporate\nevents, trade shows, theatrical sets, and themed attractions. The role involves interpreting design\nsketches or blueprints and using a combination of CNC-cut components and skilled manual hand-carving\nto produce visually stunning, durable, and lightweight props.\nKey Responsibilities\n• Foam Carving & Shaping: Carve, shape, and sculpt foam (EPS, PU) into 3D models using 3D\nrobots, hot wire cutters, rasps, rotary tools, and hand saws.\n\n• Blueprint Interpretation: Analyze technical drawings, 3D models, or artistic sketches to translate\nconcepts into accurately scaled, physical props.\n\n• Structural Assembly: Assemble multiple foam blocks, gluing, fitting, and clamping parts to create\nlarge-scale structures, ensuring structural integrity for transport and installation.\n\n• Detailing & Finishing: Apply fine details to foam surfaces using hand tools (e.g., Dremel tools) to\ncreate textures like wood grain, stone, or character features.\n\n• Surface Coating: Apply hard-coating materials (such as polyurea, epoxy resins, or sand-coat) to\nensure durability for indoor/outdoor display.\n\n• Collaboration: Work closely with designers, painters, and welders to integrate steel armatures or\nelectrical components into foam sculptures.\n\n• Tool Maintenance & Safety: Clean, and maintain specialized workshop machinery (hot wires,\nCNC routers, grinders) and adhering to strict safety protocols and PPE requirements.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of professional experience in foam sculpting, prop-making, or scenic art,\npreferably in the event or film industry.\n\n• Technical Proficiency: Expert skill with hand-carving tools, operating 3D robots, hot wires,\nsanders, and adhesive applications.\n\n• Spatial Awareness: Exceptional ability to visualize 3D forms from 2D drawings or CAD data.\n\n• Artistic Talent: Strong understanding of form, texture, and proportion, proficiency in scenic\npainting and texturing techniques.\n\n• Efficiency: Ability to work quickly to meet strict event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Stamina: Ability to stand for long periods and handle large materials.\n\n\fIdeal Candidate Profile:\n• Adaptable to fast-paced, high-pressure, and changing project requirements.\n\n• Strong problem-solving skills, capable of identifying potential issues before fabrication.\n\n• A \"can-do\" attitude with a focus on delivering high-quality, creative, and safe products.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop and site environment, which may include loud\nnoise, dust, and heat.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-steel-team-leader": "Steel Fabrication Team Leader Job description\nThe Steel Fabrication Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the Steel\nFabrication section in the event fabrication workshop, ensuring that scenic elements, structures, custom\ndisplays, and related furniture are fabricated efficiently, safely, and to high-quality standards. This handson role involves leading a team of steel fabricators and welders, acting as the primary link between the\nProduction Managers/Designers and the workshop floor.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and goals.\n\n2. Production & Operational Efficiency\n• Technical Interpretation: Read and interpret CAD drawings, blueprints, and engineering\nspecifications to ensure accurate fabrication.\n\n• Fabrication & Assembly: Cut, shape, weld, and perform grinding and finishing to ensure smooth,\naesthetically pleasing, or paint-ready finishes for public-facing structures and steel custom\nstructures, rigging frames, scenic elements, support structures using MIG/TIG welding, grinders,\nand plasma cutters.\n\n• Quality Control: Inspect and measure finished components to ensure structural integrity and\ncompliance with safety standards before they leave the workshop.\n\n• Material Handling: Safely operate workshop machinery (brake presses, shears, drills) and material\nhandling equipment (forklifts, overhead cranes).\n\n• Coordination: Coordinate workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and\ndowntime.\n\n• Collaboration: Coordinate with on-site installation teams to ensure components fit together\nseamlessly and to update them on progress, potential delays, material issues, and sometimes lead\non-site installation or load-in/out during high-pressure times.\n\n• Maintenance: Maintain a clean, organized work area and perform routine maintenance on tools\nand machinery.\n\n\f3. Quality Control & Safety\n• Enforce strict health and safety rules, including wearing PPE and maintaining the workspace.\n\n• Inspect finished products and assemblies for defects, ensuring they meet client specifications\nbefore leaving the workshop.\n\n• Identify and resolve technical fabrication issues early to prevent delays.\n\n4. Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Ensure all equipment are maintained and in good working order.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in reading technical drawings and metal metalworking for\nscenic construction, exhibit fabrication, or a similar high-paced workshop environment.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-painting-team-leader": "Printing Team Leader Job description\nThe Painting Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the painting section in\nthe event production workshop for high-quality color matching, prepping, painting, and finishing\ncustom-built scenic elements, props, displays, and structures for events, exhibitions, and activations, in\nan efficiently, safely, and to high-quality standards. This hands-on role involves leading a team of\npainters, acting as the primary link between the production Manager / Designers and the workshop\nfloor to meet client specifications and strict production deadlines.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and\ngoals.\n\n2. Production & Operational efficiency\n• Coordination: Coordinate with workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and\ndowntime.\n\n• Technical knowledge: Interpret technical drawings, CAD drawings, and design briefs to guide\nfabrication.\n\n• Collaboration: Collaborate with project managers to update them on progress, potential\ndelays, or material issues.\n\n• Surface Preparation: Clean, sand, scrape, fill holes/cracks with putty, and prime various\nmaterials (wood, metal, foam, plastics) to ensure a smooth finish.\n\n• Application Techniques: Apply paint, enamel, varnish, and lacquers using spray guns, rollers,\nand brushes.\n\n• Specialized Finishes: Create custom scenic finishes, faux textures, and effects as required by\nscenic designers.\n\n• Color Matching: Mix and match colors to meet specific, often custom, design requirements.\n\n3.Quality Control & Safety\n• Inspect finished surfaces for imperfections, ensuring high-quality, durable, and aesthetically\npleasing results.\n\n\f• Enforce strict health, safety, and environmental rules, including wearing PPEs (respirators,\ngoggles), maintaining 5S compliant orderly workspace including proper storage/disposal of\nchemicals and use of it.\n\n4.Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Clean, maintain, and troubleshoot painting equipment, including spray booths, airbrushes, and\nair-assisted airless sprayers keeping it in good working order.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience as a team leader in a professional painting environment,\npreferably in an event, fabrication, or scenic shop.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency with various spray equipment, power tools, and sanders.\n\n• Attention to Detail: Exceptional focus on achieving high-quality, detailed finishes.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
  "workshop-maintenance-manager": "Maintenance Manager Job Description\nThe Maintenance Manager will be leading a team of maintenance technicians, developing a\nPreventative Maintenance (PM) program and oversea the daily operations, repair, and upkeep of all\nfabrication equipment, tools, and facility infrastructure, and managing external contractors to ensure\nmaximum machine reliability and safety. The goal is to minimize unexpected breakdowns, which directly\nimpact project delivery, and ensure all safety standards (e.g., OSHA) are met. Given the fast-paced,\ncustom nature of event fabrication, this role requires a blend of hands-on technical repairs and strategic\nplanning to support project deadlines.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Maintenance Strategy & Execution\n• Preventative Maintenance (PM): Develop and implement a structured PM program for all\nproduction machinery, including CNC routers, welders, saws, and pneumatic tools.\n\n• Breakdown Management: Actively troubleshoot and resolve mechanical, electrical, hydraulic,\nand pneumatic systems issues to minimize downtime.\n\n• Facility Upkeep: Manage the maintenance of the workshop building, including lighting, HVAC,\nelectrical systems, and compressed air systems.\n\n• Expansion projects: Manage future expansion projects for the workshop\n\n2. Team & Project Leadership\n• Supervision: Lead, train, and mentor maintenance staff/technicians.\n\n• Vendor Management: Negotiate contracts and manage relationships with external contractors\nfor specialized, heavy, or emergency repairs.\n\n• Inventory Control: Maintain an inventory of essential spare parts and tools, managing\nprocurement to ensure critical items are in stock.\n\n3. Safety & Compliance\n• Safety Standards: Create a high-priority safety work environment, enforcing all health and safety\nrules (OSHA/local regulations).\n\n• Inspections: Conduct daily or weekly facility walkthroughs and routine equipment inspections to\nidentify potential hazards.\n\n4. Administration & Budgeting\n• Budget Management: Create and adhere to the annual maintenance budget, including CapEx\nprojects.\n\n• Documentation: Record and track maintenance activities using a Computerized Maintenance\nManagement System (CMMS).\n\n\fRequirements and Skills\n• Experience: 10+ years of experience as a maintenance manager in industrial/manufacturing\nmaintenance, preferably in a custom fabrication environment.\n\n• Technical Knowledge: Strong understanding of electrical, mechanical, hydraulic, and pneumatic\nsystems.\n\n• Fabrication Equipment: Direct experience with CNC routers, laser cutters, woodworking\nmachines, and metalworking equipment (welding/cutting).\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, delegate tasks, and motivate workers.\n\n• Skills: Proficiency in CMMS software and Microsoft Office Suite.\n\n• Education: Bachelor's degree in mechatronics engineering.\n\n• Proactive, solution-oriented mindset with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Machine Downtime Percentage: Minimizing unexpected stoppages.\n\n• PM Completion Percentage: Adherence to the maintenance schedule.\n\n• Budget Variance: Staying within forecasted maintenance costs.\n\n• Safety Incident Rate: Maintaining an accident-free workshop.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines\nand to work on site, which may include lifting, standing for long periods, and working in varied\nconditions.",
  "workshop-production-team-leader": "Production Team Leader Job description\nThe Production Team Leader is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the event production\nworkshop, ensuring that scenic elements, structures, custom displays, and related furniture are\nfabricated efficiently, safely, and to high-quality standards. This hands-on role involves leading a team\nof carpenters, welders, painters, and junior fabricators, acting as the primary link between the Project\nManagers/Designers and the workshop floor.\nKey Responsibilities\n1. Team Leadership & Supervision\n• Lead, mentor, and motivate a high-performing workshop team to meet tight event deadlines.\n\n• Allocate daily tasks to team members based on project schedules and skill levels.\n\n• Provide training and support to staff, ensuring adherence to standard operating procedures\n(SOPs).\n\n• Run daily, short \"toolbox talks\" or stand-up meetings to discuss project status, safety, and\ngoals.\n\n2. Production & Operational Efficiency\n• Interpret technical drawings, CAD drawings, and design briefs to guide fabrication.\n\n• Coordinate workshop workflow to optimize production, reducing waste and downtime.\n\n• Support, and sometimes lead, on-site installation or load-in/out during high-pressure times.\n\n• Collaborate with project managers to update them on progress, potential delays, or material\nissues.\n\n3. Quality Control & Safety\n• Enforce strict health and safety rules, including wearing PPE and maintaining a 5S compliant,\norderly workspace.\n\n• Inspect finished products and assemblies for defects, ensuring they meet client specifications\nbefore leaving the workshop.\n\n• Identify and resolve technical fabrication issues early to prevent delays.\n\n4. Material & Resource Management\n• Manage raw materials inventory and coordinate with purchasing for necessary items.\n\n• Ensure all equipment (saws, welders, routers, …) are maintained and in good working order.\n\n\fRequired Skills & Qualifications\n• Experience: 5+ years of experience in scenic construction, exhibit fabrication, or a similar highpaced workshop environment.\n\n• Leadership: Proven ability to lead a team, with strong interpersonal and communication skills.\n\n• Technical Skills: Proficiency in reading technical drawings and experience with woodworking,\nmetalworking, or scenic painting.\n\n• Software: Basic knowledge of ERP systems or inventory software is a plus, along with Microsoft\nOffice/Excel for reporting.\n\n• Problem-Solving: Strong \"hands-on\" problem-solving ability in high-pressure situations.\n\nPersonal Traits\n• Calm under pressure and able to meet strict deadlines.\n\n• Proactive, and highly organized.\n\n• Safety-conscious and a \"role model\" for team behavior.\n\nKey Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n• Project Delivery: On-time completion of fabrication tasks.\n\n• Quality: Low rate of rework or defective items.\n\n• Efficiency: Meeting budgeted hours for fabrication projects.\n\n• Safety: Zero reportable incidents.\n\nTypical Working Conditions\n• Environment: Must be able to work in a workshop environment, which may include loud noise,\ndust, and heat, with some on-site installation work.\n\n• Hours: May require working evenings, weekends, and holidays to meet event deadlines.\n\n• Physical Requirements: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and handle tight deadlines.",
};
